Vivien ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vivien","meanings":["Earlier generally taken as a variant of the boy's name   Vivian  , but now also rarely used for boys. This spelling was quite common in Old French. Its use as a girl's name in the English-speaking world was influenced by  Tennyson's  Merlin and Vivien (  1859 ). This name, from Arthurian legend, may represent an altered form of a Celtic name (perhaps akin to the Irish Gaelic name <i>Béibhinn</i> ‘white lady’, pronounced ‘bee-<b>veen</b>’). The actress  Vivien Leigh  (  1913–67 ) was christened <i>Vivian</i>."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hilduin IV de Ramerupt de Montdidier was born on 22 June 1010, in Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, France, his father, Hilduin III de Ponthieu Comte Montdidier Arces Ramerupt et Mortagne, was 36 and his mother, Anonima de Bar- Sur- Aube, was 39. He died on 15 November 1063, in Ramerupt, Aube, Champagne-Ardenne, France, at the age of 53."},"et":{"22 June 1010–15 November 1063":"22. juuni 1010–15. november 1063","1010–1063":"1010–1063","0974–1037":"0974–1037","0971–1058":"0971–1058","0974":"0974","22 June 1010":"22. juuni 1010","1037":"1037","1058":"1058","0971":"0971","15 November 1063":"15. november 1063","1010":"1010","about 1037":"umbes 1037","1063":"1063","1033-1063":"1033 kuni 1063","Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, France":"Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Ramerupt, Aube, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Ramerupt, Aube, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa","Ramerupt, Aube, Champagne-Ardennnes, France":"Ramerupt, Aube, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa","Roucy, Aisne, Picardie, France":"Roucy, Aisne, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"22 June 1010–1